The reference.tif for this test must be generated locally (run the test
once and copy the produced render into ref/reference.tif). The expected
output is a sphere whose base_color is the world position read through
coordSys "shifted" (translated by (-0.5, 0, 0) in world space). The red
channel of the rendered sphere will be brighter on the right side because
the coordSys remap adds +0.5 to world.x before it becomes the red
component. Verify visually that disabling the coordSys binding makes the
sphere render with a symmetric red gradient instead.
